b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe46083.htm)  [Next](sbe46085.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983846/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_Vedic Hymns, Part II (SBE46)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg [1897], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 289\n\n### MA _N_ _D_ ALA III, HYMN 24.\n\n#### ASH _T_ AKA III, ADHY\xc3\x82YA 1, VARGA 24.\n\n1\\. Agni, be victorious in battles; thrust away the plotters. Difficult to\novercome, overcoming malign powers, bestow splendour on (the worshipper) who\nfits out the sacrifice as a vehicle [1](sbe46084.htm#an_3:24:1:1).\n\n2\\. Agni, thou art kindled with nourishment [1](sbe46084.htm#an_3:24:2:1), the\nimmortal offerer of a feast (to the gods). Accept graciously our worship.\n\n3\\. Agni, wakeful one, son of strength, into whom offerings are poured, sit\ndown with thy splendour on this sacrificial grass of mine.\n\n4\\. Agni, together with all Agnis, with the gods exalt our prayers and those\nwho are respectful at the sacrifices.\n\n5\\. Agni, give wealth to the worshipper, abundance in valiant men; further us\n[1](sbe46084.htm#an_3:24:5:1) that we may be rich in sons.\n\n#### NOTES.\n\nThe _Ri_ shi is Vi _s_ vamitra. the metre Gayatri, the first verse Anush _t_\nubh. On this combination of a beginning Anush _t_ ubh with Gayatris following,\ncomp. H. O., Die Hymnen des Rig-veda, vol. i, p. 148.--Verse 1 = VS. IX, 37.\nVerse 5 = TS. II, 2, 12, 6; MS. IV, 12, 2; 14, 6.\n\np. 290\n\n##### Verse 1.\n\nNote 1. See above, III, 8, 3, and on ya _g_ _\xc3\xb1_ avahas, I, 127, 8, note 1;\nBergaigne, Religion Vedique, II, 287, note 2.\n\n##### Verse 2.\n\nNote 1. I _l_ a\xc2\xb4: especially designating the nourishment coming from the cow\n(personified as I _l_ a), such as ghee.\n\n##### Verse 5.\n\nNote 1. Literally, 'sharpen us.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 25](sbe46085.htm)\n\n"